trans-unit.source: Represents the AppSequence header defined in the WS-Discovery protocol.
This class allows a receiver of discovery messages to process those messages in order even though they were received out of order.

Gets a value that indicates whether the specified <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance is comparable to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance.
The discovery message sequence to compare.
`true` if the two discovery message sequences are comparable; otherwise `false`.

Compares the specified <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance with the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance.
The discovery message sequence to compare.
0 if the two discovery message sequences are equal, a negative number if the message number of other is greater than the message number of the current discovery sequence.
Determines if the specified object is equal to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance.
The object to compare.
true if the specified object is equal to the current discovery message sequence.

Determines if the specified <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance is comparable to the current <xref href="System.ServiceModel.Discovery.DiscoveryMessageSequence"></xref> instance.

`true` if the two discovery message sequences are comparable; otherwise, `false`.
